		{
			"type": "action",
			"name": "Eerie Scream",
			"system": {
				"actionType": {
					"value": "action"
				},
				"description": {
					"value": "<p><strong>Requirements</strong> The bruxa isn't in direct sunlight.</p><hr /><p>The bruxa emits a eerie scream, targeting all living creatures within 30 feet. Affected creatures must attempt at a @Check[will|dc:25|options:damaging-effect,area-effect] save or take @Damage[4d6[sonic]|options:area-damage] damage. Once used, the bruxa can't use Eerie Scream again for [[/gmr 1d6 #Duration]]{1d6 rounds}.</p><p></p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p><p><strong>Success</strong> the Creature takes half damage and is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.i3OJZU2nk64Df3xm]{Clumsy 1} until the end of its next turn.</p><p><strong>Failure</strong> the Creature takes full damage is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.TBSHQspnbcqxsmjL]{Frightened 1}</p><p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> the Creature takes doulbe damage and is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.TBSHQspnbcqxsmjL]{Frightened 2}</p>",
